{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"getNormalForm","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"() -> "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/VariantRef","preciseIdentifier":"s:4GLib10VariantRefV","text":"VariantRef"},{"kind":"text","text":"!"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"value"},{"text":" is already trusted to be in normal form then a new","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"reference to "},{"code":"value","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is returned.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"value"},{"type":"text","text":" is not already trusted, then it is scanned to check if it"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"is in normal form.  If it is found to be in normal form then it is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"marked as trusted and a new reference to it is returned."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If "},{"code":"value","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is found not to be in normal form then a new trusted","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Variant","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" is created with the same value as ","type":"text"},{"code":"value","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":". The non-normal parts of"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"value","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" will be replaced with default values which are guaranteed to be in","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"normal form."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It makes sense to call this function if you’ve received "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Variant","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"data from untrusted sources and you want to ensure your serialized"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"output is definitely in normal form.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"value"},{"type":"text","text":" is already in normal form, a new reference will be returned"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"(which will be floating if ","type":"text"},{"code":"value","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is floating). If it is not in normal form,"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the newly created "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Variant","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" will be returned with a single non-floating"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"reference. Typically, "},{"code":"g_variant_take_ref()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" should be called on the return","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"value from this function to guarantee ownership of a single non-floating","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"reference to it."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"kind":"symbol","sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/VariantRef","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/VariantRef\/VariantProtocol-Implementations"]]},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/VariantRef\/getNormalForm()","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"abstract":[{"text":"Gets a ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Variant","isActive":true},{"text":" instance that has the same value as ","type":"text"},{"code":"value","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" an